First Price:

Highest Bidder Wins

Second Price:

Highest bidder wins, pays the price of second highest bidder

Ascending:

Bidding rounds until only one bidder can bid (In case that never happens, go back to the previous round and hold a tie break on that value)

Descending:
Auction value goes down, first person to call in on that value wins.


